===Etymology===
{{rfe|zh|Related to [[火]], PST {{m|sit-pro|*məj}}?}}
{{der|zh|sit}}. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} proposes two possibilities:
* Cognate with {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*ʔ-mu²||soot; acrid (smoke)}}. If related, a merger of Minimal Old Chinese *ə with *o must have occurred.
* Cognate with {{cog|lus|mang|tr=maŋᴿ}}, {{m|lus|man|tr=manᴸ|t=sooty}}, {{cog|lus|mang|tr=maŋᴴ|t=partially burnt wood}}.
{{och-l|文}} may be a derivation with ''-n'' nominal suffix. {{och-l|黑|black}} may be an allofam. Unrelated to {{och-l|晦|dark}} according to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}.

